<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOME SEE NO HUMOR IN 'SEE NO EVIL'
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I am debating whether to see the new movie comedy smash, "See No Evil, Hear No
Evil" or wait for the sequel, which is sure to be on the drawing boards.
</P>
<P>
Can you imagine what the stars, Richard Pryor and Gene Wilder (who play a blind
man and a deaf man, respectively) and producer Marvin Worth and director Arthur
Hiller could do with epilepsy, Parkinson's disease and Alzheimer's disease?
Wouldn't those be blockbusters?
</P>
<P>
And kudos to such eminent critics as Kevin Thomas (May 12 review) for
possessing a sense of humor that I obviously lack.
</P>
<P>
Is there no decency left in a society in search of the dollar?
</P>
<P>
NORMAN LITTER
</P>
<P>
Beverly Hills
</P>
</TEXT>
