</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
. . . Will Richard Pryor and Gene Wilder do it again? We're told that there are
discussions at Tri-Star about a fourth Pryor-Wilder comedy teaming, titled
"Another You," and that Peter Bogdanovich is a possibility to direct. The
actors teamed for last year's "See No Evil, Hear No Evil," as well as "Stir
Crazy" (1980) and "Silver Streak" (1976).
</P>
<P>
. . . Ever wonder who would win a battle between the monster from "Alien" and
the title nasty from "Predator"? Look for the answer in "Predator II: Body
Count" (due at Christmas), which features the predator's trophy case -- filled
with the skulls of his human and inhuman victims, including one that's
unmistakably that of the Alien.
</P>
