<LEADPARA>  Actor Gene Wilder premiered his new movie "Another You" during a $100,000
fund-raiser for a cancer center named after his wife, Gilda Radner, who died
two years ago of ovarian cancer.;    Elizabeth Perkins, Whoopi Goldberg,
Vanessa Williams and Leonard Nimoy were among 750 people attending Monday
night's inaugural for the Gilda Radner Ovarian Cancer Detection Center at
Cedars-Sinai Medical Center in Los Angeles.  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Front  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  GIFT FOR GILDA HELPS HOSPITAL  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  People.  </MEMO>
<TEXT>     "Helping to save other Gildas sort of became my motivating force over the
past two years," Wilder said Tuesday. "This has helped me. When she died, I
was filled with frustration.";    A simple blood test might have detected
Radner's cancer 10 months earlier and possibly saved her life, Wilder said.;
 "I think Gilda would have been most happy to lend her name to this," Wilder
said.  </TEXT>
